in secondary stroke prevention: systematic review and meta- analysis of randomized controlled clinical trials. Circulation 2021;143:2441-2453. doi:"},{"num":"782","text":"37. Naqvi IA, Kamal AK, Rehman H. Multiple versus fewer antiplatelet agents for preventing early recurrence after ischaemic stroke or transient ischaemic attack. Cochrane Database Syst Rev 2020;8:Cd009716. doi: 10. 1002/14651858.CD009716.pub2."},{"num":"38","text":"Liu L, Wong KS, Leng X, et al. Dual antiplatelet therapy in stroke and ICAS: Subgroup analysis of CHANCE. Neurology 2015;85:1154-1162. doi: 10.1212/wnl.0000000 000001972."},{"num":"39","text":"Bulwa Z, Saleh Velez FG, Brorson JR,Pinto CB. Ipsilateral nonstenotic carotid disease in minor ischemic stroke: an exploratory analysis of the POINT randomized clinical trial. J Stroke Cerebrovasc Dis 2020;29:105115. doi:"},{"num":"652","text":"doi: 10.1161/ATVBAHA.118.311963."}],"id":"g014","year":2022,"topic":"antiplatelet","superseded_by":"2022_2.V4(2)-53-60--20240227.pdf"},{"filename":"2022_The2020TaiwanStrokeSocietyGuidelines.pdf","title":"The 2020 Taiwan Stroke Society Guidelines for Secondary Stroke Prevention of Non-cardioembolic Ischemic Stroke","lang":"en","garbled":false,"sections":[{"heading":"Chun-JenLina,b,Chih-PingChunga,b,*,Hao-MingChengb,c,d,","page":1,"content":"","refs":[],"subsections":[]},{"heading":"Chi-HungLiue,Li-ChiHsua,b,Nai-FangChia,b,","page":1,"content":"","refs":[],"subsections":[]},{"heading":"Sung-ChunTangf,Jiunn-TayLeeg,HelenL.Poh,","page":1,"content":"","refs":[],"subsections":[]},{"heading":"Jiann-ShingJengf,Tzung-DauWangi,I-HuiLeea,b,Taiwan","page":1,"content":"","refs":[],"subsections":[]},{"heading":"StrokeSocietyGuidelinesConsensusGroup","page":1,"content":"a DepartmentofNeurology,NeurologicalInstitute,TaipeiVeteransGeneralHospital,Taipei,Taiwan b DepartmentofMedicine,NationalYangMingChiaoTungUniversityCollegeofMedicine,Taipei, Taiwan c InstituteofPublicHealth,NationalYangMingChiaoTungUniversityCollegeofMedici